block content
  // Short summary
  header(id='particles-js-light' class='particles')
  div(class="line-background")
  section(id="intro" class='intro slanted')
    .content
      h2 SINGULARITY
      p 
        | The theme of this year's conference is 
        span(class="accent") SINGULARIT
        |: The technological singular-ity. Singularity is a term that has its origin in mathematics:
        | There, it means 'the point where 
        span(class="accent") humanity
        | will no longer be able to know what is being calculated'.
        | The past decennia, the term has been used more and more in the world of 
        span(class="accent") technology
        |.
    

  // Inspirational quote
  section(class='')
    //div(class="skewed-background-2")
    .content
      p 
        span(class="accent") “Everyone 
        |  takes the limits of his 
        span(class="accent") own 
      p(style="padding-left: 100px;")
        | vision for the 
        span(class="accent") limits 
        |  of the 
        span(class="accent") world”
        |.
      p(style="text-align: right;")
        | - Arthur 
        span(class="accent") Schopenhauer 
        
        
    div(id="speakers" class="skew-content")
      section#speakers.slanted.twocolumn
        .subpage(class="congres-bg location-content")
          .content(style="transform: skewY(-5deg);")
            div(class="header-title" style="text-align: left;") Speakers
            p(class="speakers" style="float: left; text-align: left;")
              |
              span(class="accent") SingularIT 
              | tries to change the 
              span(class="accent") minds 
              | of the students attending the conference.
              | We want to inform the attendees about how the IT 
              span(class="accent") industry 
              | might change in the coming years.
              | This will be done with interesting talks by 
              span(class="accent") scientists, 
              | entrepreneurs and experts from the business sector.
              | We have two keynote speakers and two 
              span(class="accent") parallel tracks 
              | of three sessions to fit everybody's personal needs.
              | You will be able to choose whichever talk you find more appealing. 
        .subpage.image

  div(id="location" class="skew-content")
    section#location.slanted.twocolumn
      .subpage.image
      .subpage(class="congres-bg location-content")
        .content(style="transform: skewY(-5deg);")
          div(class="header-title") Location
          p(class="location")
            | The conference will be held in 
            span(class="accent") Philharmonie Haarlem 
            | in Haarlem. 
            | It will take place on 
            span(class="accent") November 20th, 2018.

  div(id="about" class="skewed-background-2")
  header(id='particles-js-light-2' class='particles')
  section(class='intro slanted')
    .content
      h2 SNIC
      // div(role='separator' class='separator')
      p 
        span(class="accent") SNIC 
        | is an acronym for Stichting Nationaal Informatica congres (foundation national computer science conference).
        | This organisation was established in 
        span(class="accent") 2004 
        | with the purpose of stimulating the interest in IT knowledge, IT applications and the business side of it.
        | Every year, a 
        span(class="accent") conference 
        | with an IT related subject is organised. For each conference one study association is chosen to take care of the organisation.
        | This year, the organisation is in the hands of study assocation 
        span(class="accent") VIA
        |
